    question: 'Your digital wallet uses fingerprint recognition for transaction authorisation. If this biometric data is breached, why is it uniquely more severe than a password breach of equivalent scale?',
    options: ['Fingerprints are not covered under PDPO and therefore create no legal liability','Biometric data is uniquely irreplaceable — you cannot reset a fingerprint like a password','Fingerprint data has no commercial value on dark web markets','Biometric breaches only affect elderly users who cannot use mobile devices'],
