    explanation: 'This is a Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA) vulnerability — ranked #1 in the OWASP API Security Top 10 — identical in concept to IDOR but specifically in the API context. The endpoint `GET /api/v1/accounts/{id}/balance` accepts any sequential account ID and returns balance data without verifying that the authenticated user requesting the data is the owner of that account ID. A correctly implemented API must enforce authorisation at the object level: the backend must validate at request time that the authenticated user\'s identity matches the account owner of the requested resource. TLS encryption secures data in transit but does not prevent an authenticated user from querying objects they don\'t own. Rate limiting would slow but not stop enumeration — an attacker willing to spread requests over hours can still enumerate all accounts. Cleartext database storage is a separate vulnerability unrelated to the authorisation check. BOLA attacks are alarming because they require only a valid token and knowledge of the endpoint structure, both of which may be discoverable from app decompilation. For API security, mandatory server-side authorisation checks on every object-level query are non-negotiable. Review: Module 2 — Slide 4.',
